# Forge Frontend ‚Äî Windsurf Rules

You are working on the Forge frontend: the mentorship management system for the KamiLimu programme in Kenya. Read `README.md` for full project context. Read `CONVECTIONS.md` for the complete code and design standards.

## Stack

- React 18 + TypeScript strict mode + Vite + Tailwind CSS
- Design tokens in `src/styles/global.css` ‚Äî never hardcode a hex value or pixel value
- `font-mono` = JetBrains Mono (headings, labels, buttons, captions)
- `font-sans` = Hind Guntur (body text, subtitles, descriptions)
- API documentation at `http://localhost:8000/api/v1/docs`

## What Is Already Built ‚Äî Do Not Rebuild

- `src/lib/api.ts` ‚Äî The only API client. Exports `api` (`api.auth.*`, `api.users.*`) and `tokenStore`. Never use `fetch()` anywhere else.
- `src/types/auth.ts` ‚Äî All auth and user type definitions. Add new types to `src/types/` in their own file.
- `src/hooks/useAuth.ts` ‚Äî Auth context and `useAuth()` hook. Do not create another auth state mechanism.
- `src/pages/Login.tsx`, `Activate.tsx`, `ForgotPassword.tsx`, `ResetPassword.tsx` ‚Äî Complete. Do not rebuild.
- `src/components/ui/Button.tsx`, `Input.tsx`, `Spinner.tsx` ‚Äî Exist. Check `src/components/README.md` before building any component.

## Non-negotiable Rules

### Components
- Props interface above every component
- Named exports only ‚Äî no `export default`
- Business logic in `src/hooks/` ‚Äî components call hooks and render, nothing else
- All four states handled: loading, empty, error, success
- Every new component has a `.stories.tsx` file alongside it in the same folder

### Styling
- Never hardcode a hex value: use `text-teal-500`, `bg-auburn`, `text-text-primary` etc.
- Never hardcode a pixel value: use `gap-4`, `px-6`, `mt-8` etc.
- Mobile-first: write for 375px first, then `md:` and `lg:` breakpoints

### API
- `import { api } from '@/lib/api'` ‚Äî always. Never `fetch()` in a component or hook.
- New API response shapes go in `src/types/` in a dedicated file

### TypeScript
- Strict mode is on ‚Äî zero `any`. Use `unknown` and narrow.
- Every hook has typed parameters and a typed return value

### Async form handlers
- Wrap async handlers on form `onSubmit` in `void`:
  `onSubmit={(e) => { void handleSubmit(e) }}`

## File Locations

```
src/components/ui/      Generic reusable ‚Äî Button, Input, Spinner, Badge, Card‚Ä¶
src/components/forge/   Forge domain ‚Äî SessionRow, GraduationStatus, TrackBadge‚Ä¶
src/components/layout/  Shell ‚Äî Sidebar, TopBar, PageWrapper
src/hooks/              All custom hooks ‚Äî business logic lives here
src/lib/api.ts          The only API client
src/types/              TypeScript types for all API shapes
src/pages/              One file per route
```
